					<div id="post_message_1545386">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Yes, that's how it works. Has to be a unanimous vote otherwise it doesn't pass, from all the mods. <br />
<br />
I don't think the mods have to make themselves publicly known, but as before I'll go through my reasoning. As previously, I'm voting yes. I've tried to be patient, I'm ignoring the various insults he flings my way (come on, misspelling my name in the same way my guild does at least once a week by accident is hardly Oscar Wilde wit), but I honestly don't see any other option at this point. Either we abandon the ruleset completely, admit that folks should be able to say absolutely what they want under any circumstances, or we remove Dmitry. Whatever point he intended to make is buried beneath the chilidish trolling and rampant homophobia that makes this place unpleasant to visit, and frankly, as an adult I don't give much time to people whose only means of arguing is by  shouting &quot;homoloving bumfucks&quot; at people. Whatever people think about the changing moderation of Graffes over the years, I don't think we've ever allowed the word f****t to be flung around with glee to wind people up. And changing it to faygoat doesn't fool a 6 year old. <br />
<br />
After a while, you realise it's not actually a point he's trying to make. It's just a game, and screw anyone else whose involved as long as he gets his fun. I was more than happy to forget the suspension period - mods had voted, he wasn't to be banned, <b>case closed</b>. But he came back and immediately started doing the same thing. Despite various conversations with folks asking him not to act like that, he's continued doing it and we're again looking at having to suspend him for the same stuff. <br />
<br />
No, the rules system is not perfect, and the moderation can be erratic - that's a given in any system that uses people and relies on judgement like ours does. But it's a lot better than what it was 4 years ago, when the moderation was subject to personal whims and vindictive campaigns by mods against posters they didn't like. But you don't get things changed by behaving like Dmitry has done. We have an open system to allow rules changes, we have elections to put up mods who we think will do a decent job. We don't go absolutely nucleur over a thread title change and then start a campaign of spamming the forums with bigoted crap for giggles for 4 months.<br />
<br />
(It's also worth noting that other than the official warning given to Ianylien over his use of the word, Dmitry has been the SOLE person to have been warned or suspended under this rule, or had swathes of posts having to be deleted. This rule is one that is enforced so rarely it isn't true).
