If Dmitry is banned, it will validate everything he has said about Graffe's administration: that it has become nothing more than a glorified instrument of a lynch mob set out to dictate political correctness. While I have found much of Dmitry's behavior detestable, I find this gross -- and public -- display of administrative narcissism extremely over the line. Administrators and moderators should never tolerate a public &quot;movement&quot; to get another user banned.<br />
 <br />
Moderators have said in the very discussion thread that Voca listed that they would not vote to ban them. Reviewing the thread, Layonya very publicly states that she would vote &quot;no&quot; to perma-ban Dmitry. I hope that she lives up to her public commitment, and stops this charade before we turn Graffe's into a bland circle-jerk of one-opinion.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
